5 (b) (1) Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection and notwithstanding any
6 other provision of law, a hospital offering bone marrow transplant services shall allow an
7 individual to donate bone marrow to any individual.
8 (2) An individual may donate bone marrow to another individual if a
9 licensed physician determines, based on the physician’s medical judgment, that the
10 donation of the bone marrow is in the best interests of the donee and there is no substantial
11 risk of medical injury to the donor.
12 (C) NOTWITHSTANDING ANY OTHER PROVISION OF LAW, A HOSPITAL SHALL
13 ALLOW AN INDIVIDUAL RECEIVING A MEDICAL PROCEDURE TO PROVIDE AN
14 AUTOLOGOUS OR DIRECTED BLOOD DONATION ORDERED BY A PHYSICIAN FOR THE
15 MEDICAL PROCEDURE IF THE HOSPITAL FACILITATES BLOOD DONATIONS.
